                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="105r" to="114r" facs="107"/>
                        <title type="complete" corresp="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"/>
                        <note>Psalm 118 has a very unique set of explanations of the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew alphabet</note>


                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                  <locus target="#174v" facs="177"/>
                  <q>“This book was finished in the month of Mäskäräm on Friday in the year of Luke, the Evangelist, in the reign of Iyassu by the hand of Silondis, sinner and unclean.
                    May this book heal body and soul, forever and ever, Amen.”</q>
                    <note>Iyasu IV reigned 18 June 1830 through18 March 1832. When we correlate the year of Luke with the dates,
                    it would indicate completion in the year 1832 between September 10 and October 9. Iyasu III reigned 16 Feb 1784 through 24 April 1788. When we correlate the year of Luke with his dates,
                    it would indicate completion in the year 1786 between September 9 and October 8</note>
                  </colophon>

                </msItem>
